intro: Cheniella didyma, commonly known as the twin-leaf cheniella, is a flowering plant belonging to the family Apiaceae. It is characterized by its small, delicate flowers that typically bloom in clusters. The plant has finely divided leaves that resemble those of other members of its family, such as carrots and parsley. It is native to certain regions of South America and thrives in moist, temperate climates. Cheniella didyma is often found in shaded, woodland environments where it contributes to the understory vegetation.
